In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce.

Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and cut half the @Yellow Onion{1} (whole onion for 4 servings) into 1/2-inch-thick wedges. Mince one wedge until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Mince @Cilantro{1/4%oz}(minced).

== Salsa Fresca ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, and a big squeeze of lime juice; season with @salt{}.

== Smoky Red Pepper Crema ==

Add @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tbsp} to a separate small bowl. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Charred Poblano and Onion ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} (use a #large pan{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add poblano and onion wedges. Season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred, ~{7-9%minutes}.

Transfer to a plate.

== Saucy Spiced Ground Pork ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Pork{10%oz} and a big pinch of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex Paste{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings) until combined. Bring to a simmer and cook until mixture is saucy and pork is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest and half the cilantro. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) for extra richness.

Divide rice between bowls and top with veggies, saucy pork, any remaining sauce from pan, salsa, crema, and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.